{
  "_DRAFT_NOTE": "AGENT-DRAFTED 2026-05-06 per SB-095 — DRAFT v1, NOT operator-confirmed. Phase 7 of UX-design pass: narrow-terminal variant of profile-aidlc-stamp-full (t5 review tier). Same 4-line architecture-grouped layout (action / objective / telemetry / env+audit) with reduced widget density per line so total width fits ~100-char terminals. Drops: L1-model (already on L3) · L1-stage (SFIF carries the phase signal) · L3-session-name · L3-thinking · L3-vim · L4-weeklyusage · L4-sescost. Mission/focus widgets keep their 80-char smart-abbrev budget — operators on truly narrow terminals see graceful truncation via ccstatusline flex (last-resort).",
  "_TIER": "t5-narrow — 4-line review variant for narrow terminals (~100 chars)",
  "_USE_CASE": "Review/audit on narrow terminal — when operator needs full AIDLC + objective + audit visibility but can't afford the full t5 widget density.",
